    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Interesting. I've heard some legal scholars argue that focusing only on these rights might overstep what the Constitution actually says, and that \"due process\" should only be about the fairness of legal procedures rather than the substance of the laws. Do you think those critics are right to be concerned about judicial overreach?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
