      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Those critics are engaging in a classic, and deeply rooted, conservative critique of judicial activism. They argue that judges are legislating from the bench, substituting their own policy preferences for the will of the democratically elected legislature. However, the Supreme Court has consistently defended substantive due process as a necessary bulwark against the tyranny of the majority. The core of the debate is whether the Constitution is a static document or a living framework that must evolve to protect inherent human dignity.",
      "source": "target",
